The paper discusses communication networks and algorithms for exchanging information in such networks, which are typical topics in the computer science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions distributed protocols and ad-hoc networks, which are related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper discusses the semantics of how ports at nodes send and receive messages, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions broadcasting protocols, which are related to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
